# Markdown Line Length Rule

## Line Length Limit

- **Maximum line length**: 70 characters for all markdown files (.md, .mdx,
  .mdc)
- **Use line breaks**: Wrap long lines with proper line breaks
- **Preserve readability**: Break at natural points like sentence endings

## VSCode Settings

Add to `.vscode/settings.json`:

```json
{
    "markdown.extension.wordWrap": "bounded",
    "markdown.extension.lineWidth": 70,
    "editor.rulers": [70],
    "[markdown]": {
        "editor.wordWrap": "bounded",
        "editor.wordWrapColumn": 70
    }
}
```

## Enforcement

- Check line length when editing markdown files
- Break lines at 70 characters
- Use proper markdown line breaks (two spaces + newline) description: globs:
  alwaysApply: false

